25|$|Single <b>malt</b> <b>whisky</b> is {{associated}} with the Scottish tradition, although there are also Irish and other single malts. Penderyn, the only whisky commercially produced in Wales, is also a single malt.|$|E
25|$|To {{be called}} a single <b>malt</b> <b>whisky</b> in Scotland, a bottle may only contain whisky {{distilled}} from malted barley and produced at a single distillery. The regulations of other countries may allow malted rye.|$|E
50|$|Although {{conceived}} for wine, other alcoholic beverages, such as cognac {{or single}} <b>malt</b> Scotch <b>whisky,</b> are often stored {{and served in}} stoppered decanters. Certain cognacs and <b>malt</b> <b>whiskies</b> are sold in decanters such as the 50-year-old single malt Dalmore or the Bowmore Distillery 22 Year Old.|$|R
